journalctl	                                    show all entries
journalctl -b	                                  Show boot-related messages
journalctl  -ef	                                Jump to the end of the journal and enable follow mode
journalctl -o verbose	                          Show all fields stored in the systemd journal
journalctl  -k	                                Show Kernel messages
journalctl _SYSTEMD_UNIT=service_name.service	  Show all messages generated by a service
journalctl _PID=1234	                          Show all messages generated by a PID
journalctl  --disk-usage	                      Current disk usage
journalctl  --vacuum-size=1G	                  Shrink the journal by a specified size
